16 (2)(a) An urban enterprise zone may consist of a total area of not more than 12 square miles in
17 size.
18 (b) A rural enterprise zone may consist of a total area of not more than 15 square miles in size.
19 (c) For purposes of this subsection, the area of the zone must be calculated by excluding that
20 portion of the zone that lies below the ordinary high water mark of a navigable body of water.
21 (3) Except as provided in subsection (4) of this section:
22 (a) An urban enterprise zone must have 12 miles or less, and a rural enterprise zone must have
23 15 miles or less, as the greatest distance between any two points within the zone; and
24 (b) Unconnected areas of an enterprise zone may not be more than five miles apart.
25 (4) Unconnected areas of a rural enterprise zone may not be more than 15 miles apart when an
26 unconnected area is entirely within a sparsely populated county, and the zone:
27 (a) Must have 20 miles or less as the greatest distance between any two points within the zone,
28 if only a portion of the zone is contained within a sparsely populated county; or
29 (b) Must have 25 miles or less as the greatest distance between any two points within the zone,
30 if the zone is entirely contained within a sparsely populated county.
31 (5) This section does not apply to the designation or redesignation of a reservation enterprise
32 zone or a reservation partnership zone.
