30 (b) The firm has made the commitments and provided the other information required under
31 subsection (2) of this section.
32 (7) If the business firm seeking authorization is an eligible business firm described in ORS
33 285C.135 [(5)(b)] (4)(b), the sponsor must, as a condition of approving the application, make a formal
34 finding that the business firm is an eligible business firm under ORS 285C.135 and that the size of
35 the proposed investment, the employment at the facility of the firm or the nature of the activities
36 to be undertaken by the firm within the enterprise zone will significantly enhance the local econ-
37 omy, promote the purposes for which the zone was created and increase employment within the
38 zone.
39 (8) The approval of both the sponsor and the county assessor under this section shall be prima
40 facie evidence that the qualified property of the business firm will receive the property tax ex-
41 emption under ORS 285C.175. In approving the application, the sponsor and county assessor shall
42 provide proof of approval as directed by the Oregon Business Development Department.
43 (9) If the sponsor or county assessor fails or refuses to authorize the business firm, the business
44 firm may appeal to the Oregon Tax Court under ORS 305.404 to 305.560. The business firm shall
45 provide copies of the firm’s appeal to the sponsor, county assessor, the Department of Revenue and
[10]

B-Eng. HB 4084
1 the Oregon Business Development Department.
2 (10) Authorization under this section does not ensure that property constructed, added, modified
3 or installed by the authorized business firm will receive property tax exemption under ORS 285C.175.
4 The sponsor and the county assessor are not liable in any way if the Department of Revenue or the
5 county assessor later determines that an authorized business firm does not satisfy the requirements
6 for an exemption on qualified property.
7 (11) Notwithstanding subsection (1) of this section, if an eligible business firm has begun or
8 completed the construction, addition, modification or installation of property that meets the quali-
9 fications of ORS 285C.180, and the property has not yet been subject to property tax after having
10 been placed in service, then, for purposes of ORS 285C.050 to 285C.250, the firm shall be authorized
11 under this section if the firm files an application that is allowed under subsection (12) of this section
12 and is otherwise authorized under this section.
13 (12) Late submission of an application under this section is allowed if:
14 (a) A rule permits late submissions of applications under this section; or
15 (b) The Department of Revenue waives filing deadline requirements under this section. The de-
16 partment shall issue a letter to the eligible business firm and zone sponsor setting forth the waiver
17 under this paragraph.
18 SECTION 12. ORS 285C.180 is amended to read:
19 285C.180. (1) The following types of property are qualified for exemption under ORS 285C.175:
20 (a) A newly constructed building or structure.
21 (b) A new addition to or modification of an existing building or structure.
22 (c) Any real property machinery or equipment or personal property, whether new, used or re-
23 conditioned, that is installed on property that is owned or leased by an authorized business firm,
24 and:
25 (A) Newly purchased or leased by the firm, unless the property is described in ORS 285C.175
26 (4)(a); or
27 (B) Newly transferred into the enterprise zone from outside the county within which the site
28 of the firm is located and installed.
29 (2) Property described in subsection (1) of this section is qualified under this section only if:
30 (a) The property meets or exceeds the minimum cost requirements established under ORS
31 285C.185;
32 (b) The property satisfies applicable usage, lease or location requirements established under
33 ORS 285C.185;
34 (c) The property was constructed, added, modified or installed to further the production of in-
35 come;
36 (d) The property is owned or leased by an authorized business firm;
37 (e) The location of the property corresponds to the location as set forth in the application for
38 authorization of the business firm and consists of a single site or multiple sites adjacent to or having
39 comparable proximity to each other, within the boundaries of the enterprise zone;
40 (f) The property is the same general type of property as described in the application for au-
41 thorization; and
42 (g) In the case of an eligible business firm described in ORS 285C.135 [(5)(b)] (4)(b), the actual
43 investment at the facility of the firm is consistent with the description set forth in the application
44 for authorization.
45 (3) Notwithstanding subsection (1) of this section, the following property is not qualified for ex-
[11]

B-Eng. HB 4084
1 emption under ORS 285C.175:
2 (a) Land.
3 (b) Property that was not in use or occupancy for more than a 180-day period that ends during
4 the preceding assessment year.
5 (c) On-site developments that, consistent with ORS 307.010, are assessed as land.
6 (d) Noninventory supplies, including but not limited to lubricants.
7 (e) Any operator-driven item of machinery or equipment or any vehicle, if the item or vehicle
8 moves by internal motorized power. An item or vehicle described in this paragraph includes but is
9 not limited to an item or vehicle that moves within an enclosed space.
10 (f) Any device or rolling stock that is pulled, pushed or carried by a vehicle that is suitable as
11 a mode of transportation beyond the enterprise zone boundary.
12 (4) Subsection (3)(b) of this section does not apply to the first assessment year for which the
13 property is exempt under ORS 285C.175.
14 (5) For purposes of this section and ORS 285C.175, property includes any portion or incremental
15 unit of property that is newly constructed or installed, or that is a new addition to or modification
16 of an existing building or structure.
17 SECTION 13. ORS 285C.155 is amended to read:
18 285C.155. For purposes of ORS 285C.200 [(2)] (3):
19 (1) The sponsor of an enterprise zone, at the time authorization is sought by a business firm
20 under ORS 285C.140, shall establish a minimum number of employees the firm must maintain in the
21 enterprise zone throughout the exemption period.
22 (2) The sponsor, at the time authorization is sought by a business firm under ORS 285C.140, may
23 establish other reasonable conditions with which the firm must comply in order for qualified prop-
24 erty of the firm to be exempt under ORS 285C.175.
25 (3) Employment requirements and other conditions established by the sponsor under this section
26 shall be set forth in a resolution adopted by the governing body of the sponsor at the time the
27 sponsor approves the application of the business firm for authorization under ORS 285C.140.
28 (4) A resolution adopted pursuant to this section may be modified at the request of the business
29 firm at any time prior to the start of the first tax year for which an exemption under ORS 285C.175
30 is claimed.
31 SECTION 14. ORS 285C.205 is amended to read:
32 285C.205. The requirements of ORS 285C.200 [(2)(b)(B)] (3)(b)(B) are met if the qualified business
33 firm does all of the following:
34 (1) The firm demonstrates at least a 10 percent increase in productivity no later than 18 months
35 following January 1 of the first assessment year for which an exemption under ORS 285C.175 is
36 claimed. Unless further specified by the sponsor of the enterprise zone through the resolution
37 adopted under ORS 285C.155:
38 (a) The increase must be in business operations of the firm that are using qualified property
39 receiving the exemption;
40 (b) Productivity is measured by dividing physical units or quantity of output by the number of
41 labor hours engaged in the operations that produced the physical units or quantity of output; and
42 (c) The base level of productivity shall be established over a minimum 12-month period preceding
43 the date on which the qualified property is placed in service.
44 (2) The firm maintains or exceeds the 10 percent increase in productivity under subsection (1)
45 of this section as an annual average rate for each subsequent assessment year during the remainder
[12]

B-Eng. HB 4084
1 of the exemption period.
2 (3) On or before April 1 of each of the first three assessment years for which an exemption is
3 claimed, the firm deposits into an account established by the sponsor an amount equal to 25 percent
4 of the estimated tax savings arising from the exemption for that year. The sponsor may adopt addi-
5 tional specifications or requirements applicable to this subsection in the resolution the sponsor
6 adopts under ORS 285C.155. Consistent with this subsection and any additional specifications or
7 requirements adopted by the sponsor:
8 (a) For up to 30 months following the relevant April 1 date for which a deposit is made, the firm
9 may draw from the account amounts equal to any expense incurred for training or retraining em-
10 ployees to promote or facilitate productivity increases under this section, except that the total
11 amount withdrawn from the account for that deposit may not exceed $3,500 per trained employee;
12 (b) Any amount attributable to the deposit that remains in the account after the 30-month period
13 in which firm withdrawals may be made under paragraph (a) of this subsection shall be transferred
14 to a special fund for use by local publicly funded job training providers; and
15 (c) No more than 18 months after the deposit, the estimated tax savings on which the deposit
16 was based shall be reconciled with the actual tax savings arising from the exemption. The recon-
17 ciliation shall be accomplished by the firm immediately making a further deposit into the account
18 to cover any shortfall or by being reimbursed from the account for any surplus. A deposit or re-
19 imbursement made pursuant to this paragraph does not affect withdrawals or transfers that occur
20 as a result of paragraph (a) or (b) of this subsection.
21 SECTION 15. ORS 285C.210 is amended to read:
22 285C.210. (1) For purposes of ORS 285C.175, 285C.200 and 285C.240, except as provided in sub-
23 section (3) of this section, operations of a business firm within the enterprise zone are substantially
24 curtailed when:
25 (a) Pursuant to the initial claim of exemption and satisfaction of ORS 285C.200 (1)(c), the number
26 of employees of the firm:
27 (A) Is reduced by more than 85 percent from the highest number of employees of the firm; or
28 (B) Has been reduced by more than 50 percent from the highest number of employees of the firm
29 over two consecutive annual filing periods under ORS 285C.220 (1); or
30 (b) The annual average number of employees of the firm during the first assessment year for
31 which the exemption under ORS 285C.175 is granted, or any subsequently allowed year of exemption,
32 is reduced below the greater of:
33 (A) The annual average number of employees of the firm, averaged over the 12 months preceding
34 the date of the application for authorization, plus one employee; or
35 (B) 110 percent of the annual average number of employees of the firm, averaged over the 12
36 months preceding the date of the application for authorization.
37 (2) For the purposes of this section:
38 (a) Except as provided in paragraph (c)(A) of this subsection, the number of employees of the
39 firm is the employment of the firm, as defined in ORS 285C.200 [(7)(b)] (8)(b), on the earlier of the
40 date a claim for exemption is filed under ORS 285C.220 or April 1 of the year in which the ex-
41 emption is initially claimed under ORS 285C.175 and following each assessment year of the ex-
42 emption, including after the last such assessment year.
43 (b) Except as provided in paragraph (c)(B) of this subsection, the annual average number of
44 employees of the firm is the number of employees of the firm averaged over the course of each as-
45 sessment year in which an exemption under ORS 285C.175 is allowed, using employment figures for
[13]

B-Eng. HB 4084
1 no fewer than four equivalent periods during the year.
2 (c) For the first assessment year for which an authorized business firm that qualifies under ORS
3 285C.200 [(5)] (6) claims an exemption under ORS 285C.175, substantial curtailment under subsection
4 (1)(a)(A) or (b) of this section shall be determined by:
5 (A) Combining the number of employees of the firm and the number of employees at any appli-
6 cable site of the firm outside the enterprise zone; and
7 (B) Combining the annual average number of employees of the firm with the annual average
8 number of employees at any applicable site of the firm outside the enterprise zone.
9 (3) Operations of a business firm are not substantially curtailed under this section during a pe-
10 riod of suspension as otherwise provided in ORS 285C.203.
11 SECTION 16. There is appropriated to the Oregon Business Development Department for
12 the biennium ending June 30, 2027, out of the General Fund, the amount of $40,000,000 for
13 the purpose of carrying out section 17 of this 2026 Act.
14 SECTION 17. The Oregon Business Development Department shall deposit the moneys
15 appropriated under section 16 of this 2026 Act in the Industrial Site Loan Fund established
16 under ORS 285B.046. The moneys may be used for any purpose or program for which moneys
17 in the fund may be used.
18 SECTION 18. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
19 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
